<div id="a-tense-scene-outside-ferguson-police-department" class="updated-entry">
<h5 class="updated-marker highlight"><span class="time"><a href="#a-tense-scene-outside-ferguson-police-department">9:41 P.M.</a></span><strong>A Tense Scene Outside Ferguson Police Department</strong></h5>
</div>
<div class="updated-entry-content">
<div class="w480">
<figure class="media photo promo" itemprop="" itemscope="" itemid="https://static01.nyt.com/images/2014/11/25/us/FERGUSONBLOG-REACT1/FERGUSONBLOG-REACT1-blog480.jpg" itemtype="//schema.org/ImageObject" role="group"><span class="visually-hidden">Photo</span>
<div class="image"><img itemprop="url" itemid="https://static01.nyt.com/images/2014/11/25/us/FERGUSONBLOG-REACT1/FERGUSONBLOG-REACT1-blog480.jpg" src="https://static01.nyt.com/images/2014/11/25/us/FERGUSONBLOG-REACT1/FERGUSONBLOG-REACT1-blog480.jpg" id="100000003253970" width="480" height="320" alt="A protester in Ferguson, Mo., on Monday nightÂ reacted to the grand jury&#039;s decisionÂ not to indict Officer Darren Wilson in the fatal shooting of Michael Brown."   /><meta itemprop="height" content="320"><meta itemprop="width" content="480"></div>
<figcaption class="caption" itemprop="description"><span class="caption-text">A protester in Ferguson, Mo., on Monday nightÂ reacted to the grand jury&#8217;s decisionÂ not to indict Officer Darren Wilson in the fatal shooting of Michael Brown.</span><span class="credit" itemprop="copyrightHolder"><span class="visually-hidden">Credit</span> Whitney Curtis for The New York Times</span></figcaption>
</figure>
</div>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">As word spread that there was no indictment, the crowd of protesters outside the police station here surged forward, throwing what appeared to be a bottle and other objects at a line of police. A protester&#8217;s sign flew in the air over the heads of officers.</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">People shouted angrily and rattled the metal barricades that restricted access to the police stationâs parking lot. âShut it down!â several young men yelled.</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">The sound of glass breaking on the concrete could be heard. Police in riot shields and riot helmets stood behind the barricades as a tense stand-off ensued.</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">&#8212; <em>MANNY FERNANDEZ</em></p>
</div>
</div>
<div class="type-live-update update">
<div id="browns-family-expresses-disappointment-urges-calm" class="updated-entry">
<h5 class="updated-marker highlight"><span class="time"><a href="#browns-family-expresses-disappointment-urges-calm">9:32 P.M.</a></span><strong>Brown Family Expresses Disappointment and Urges Calm</strong></h5>
</div>
<div class="updated-entry-content">
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">Shortly after the decision was announced that a grand jury had found no probable cause to charge Officer Darren Wilson in the shooting death of  Michael Brown, Mr. Brown&#8217;s family issued a statement:</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">We are profoundly disappointed that the killer of our child will not face the consequence of his actions.</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">While we understand that many others share our pain, we ask that you channel your frustration in ways that will make a positive change.  We need to work together to fix the system that allowed this to happen.  </p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">Join with us in our campaign to ensure that every police officer working the streets in this country wears a body camera.  </p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">We respectfully ask that you please keep your protests peaceful.  Answering violence with violence is not the appropriate reaction.    </p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">Let&#8217;s not just make noise, let&#8217;s make a difference.</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">&#8212; <em>THE NEW YORK TIMES</em></p>
</div>
</div>
<div class="type-live-update update">
<div id="a-modest-gathering-at-spot-where-brown-died-2" class="updated-entry">
<h5 class="updated-marker highlight"><span class="time"><a href="#a-modest-gathering-at-spot-where-brown-died-2">8:59 P.M.</a></span><strong>A Modest Gathering at Spot Where Brown Died</strong></h5>
</div>
<div class="updated-entry-content">
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">FERGUSON, Mo. &#8212; Minutes before the grand jury&#8217;s announcement, five men, dressed almost entirely in black, walked in a circle around the memorial marking the spot where Michael Brown died.</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">Their protest was a vocal one, replete with expletives and raised voices.</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">A small group of bystanders looked on, mostly in silence.</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">&#8212; <em>ALAN BLINDER</em></p>
</div>
