<div id="prosecutor-might-ask-for-release-of-grand-jury-records" class="updated-entry">
<h5 class="updated-marker highlight"><span class="time"><a href="#prosecutor-might-ask-for-release-of-grand-jury-records">7:23 P.M.</a></span><strong>Prosecutor Could Seek Release of Grand Jury Records</strong></h5>
</div>
<div class="updated-entry-content">
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">If Officer Darren Wilson is not indicted, Robert P. McCulloch, the St. Louis County prosecutor, has said that he would ask a judge<a href="//www.nytimes.com/news/ferguson/2014/11/23/release-of-evidence-used-by-grand-jury-is-uncertain/"> to release recordings and transcripts</a> of the grand jury proceedings, which typically remain secret. Julie Bosman reported on Sunday that a St. Louis County circuit judge has not yet agreed on whether to release those records.</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">&#8212; <em>EMMA FITZSIMMONS</em></p>
</div>
</div>
<div class="type-live-update update">
<div id="browns-family-anxious-as-decision-nears" class="updated-entry">
<h5 class="updated-marker highlight"><span class="time"><a href="#browns-family-anxious-as-decision-nears">7:20 P.M.</a></span><strong>Brown&#8217;s Family Anxious as Decision Nears</strong></h5>
</div>
<div class="updated-entry-content">
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">The family of Michael Brown was notified on Monday afternoon that the grand jury had reached a decision. John Eligon<a href="//www.nytimes.com/news/ferguson/2014/11/24/parents-find-themselves-in-the-limelight/"> reported that the family</a> has been on &#8220;pins and needles&#8221; waiting for the decision. Mr. Brown&#8217;s mother, Lesley McSpadden, has said that &#8220;she has to believe that she&#8217;ll get justice for her child because that&#8217;s all she has left,&#8221; according to Benjamin L. Crump, a lawyer for the family.</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">&#8212; <em>EMMA FITZSIMMONS</em></p>
</div>
</div>
