<div id="national-guard-takes-up-positions" class="updated-entry">
<h5 class="updated-marker highlight"><span class="time"><a href="#national-guard-takes-up-positions">7:05 P.M.</a></span><strong>National Guard Soldiers Take Positions</strong></h5>
</div>
<div class="updated-entry-content">
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">FERGUSON, Mo. &#8212; Missouri National  Guard soldiers took up positions Monday evening at a law enforcement command post near the site of the most violent demonstrations in August.</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">Humvees were posted at an entrance to the command post, and a vehicle with a red cross on its side was parked nearby.</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">St. Louis County police officers and troopers from the Missouri State Highway Patrol regularly left the compound in an array of marked and unmarked vehicles.</p>
