<div id="a-terse-alert-from-the-st-louis-county-prosecutor-2" class="updated-entry">
<h5 class="updated-marker highlight"><span class="time"><a href="#a-terse-alert-from-the-st-louis-county-prosecutor-2">6:19 P.M.</a></span><strong>A Terse Alert From the St. Louis County Prosecutor</strong></h5>
</div>
<div class="updated-entry-content">
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">Edward Magee, a spokesman for the St. Louis County prosecutor, alerted reporters that the grand jury was ready to release its decision with an email that reflected the pace of the last few days.</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">&#8220;Media,&#8221; the email read. &#8220;The Grand Jury announcement concerning the Darren Wilson case will be at 8:00 P.M. this evening at the Justice Center, 100 S. Central, Clayton, Mo.  All seats have been accounted for and no one else will be allowed in the building. Please do not respond with any questions. Sorry but I have not been able to return all calls and emails the last three days.&#8221;</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">That&#8217;s 8 p.m. Central Time.</p>
</div>
</div>
<div class="type-live-update update">
<div id="anticipating-unrest-clayton-businesses-close" class="updated-entry">
<h5 class="updated-marker highlight"><span class="time"><a href="#anticipating-unrest-clayton-businesses-close">5:55 P.M.</a></span><strong>Anticipating Unrest, Clayton Businesses Close</strong></h5>
</div>
<div class="updated-entry-content">
<blockquote class="twitter-tweet tw-hide-thread">
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">Lots of businesses closed in downtown Clayton ahead of #MichaelBrown grand jury decision. #ferguson //t.co/HKkcYp8emq</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">â <a href="https://www.twitter.com/joelcurrier">joelcurrier (@joelcurrier)</a> <a href="https://www.twitter.com/joelcurrier/status/537012719811960833" data-datetime="2014-11-24T22:39:44+00:00">24 Nov 14</a></p>
</blockquote>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">Over the weekend, workers in Clayton, Mo., erected barriers around the St. Louis County Police Headquarters and prepared to change traffic patterns near the courthouse where the grand jurors meet. The moves were among a long list of <a href="//www.nytimes.com/2014/11/23/us/ferguson-grand-jury.html">measures law enforcement officials have undertaken</a> to prepare for possible civil unrest, Julie Bosman and Monica Davey have reported.</p>
</div>
</div>
<div class="type-live-update update">
